<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>3DCG: Studio Pipeline Segment</title>
    <%= stylesheets('3dcg', 'box2') %>
    <%= scripts('jquery', 'jquery-ui', 'underscore', 'ace/ace', 'source-editor') %>
    <style>
      img.large {
        width: 60%;
      }

      video {
        margin: 10px auto;
      }
    </style>

    <script type="text/x-mathjax-config">
      MathJax.Hub.Config({tex2jax: {inlineMath: [['$','$'], ['\\(','\\)']]}});
    </script>
    <script type="text/javascript" async src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/mathjax/2.7.1/MathJax.js?config=TeX-AMS_CHTML"></script>
  </head>

  <body>
    <header>
      Sutdio Pipeline Segment
    </header>
    <div id="contents">
      <section>
        <h1>Studio</h1>
        <p>
          In order to make your Chaiscript work with 3D Studio, you need to
          have it output the renderings in the correct format:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            First, the images are converted into the WIF file format.
          </li>
          <li>
            Next, this byte stream is converted to base64.
          </li>
          <li>
            Lastly, this base64 data is written to stdout.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Each of these three steps need to be repeated at the end of your Chaiscript.
          It would be more practical if there were a single pipeline segment
          that performs all three steps.
        </p>
        <aside class="boxed2">
          <h1>Task</h1>
          <p>
            Create a new pipeline segment so that you can replace the
            ``Pipeline.wif(), Pipeline.base64(), Pipeline.stdout()``
            by a single segment ``Pipeline.studio()``.
          </p>
        </aside>
      </section>      
    </div>
  </body>

  <script>
    function initialize()
    {
      SourceEditor.initialize();
    }

    $( initialize );   
  </script>
</html>
